content:
I find the US government in a very tricky spot. They want to support Ukraine by banning Russia oil (less supply).  But also want lower gasoline prices and better Energy Security.  

Right now, the approach to the energy industry appears to be more of a stick than a carrot.

content:
I find it interesting how the price of gasoline went up IMMEDIATELY on news of Russia invading Ukraine, based on oil "supply concerns."
Oil jumps to 140... ok.
Oil retreats to under 100... gas continues to rise.
Biden adds 1Mbpd to our supply... gas continues to rise.
I call BS https://t.co/0nYhihUlnS
